The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Jan. 21: With the primary market expecting public offers worth over Rs 40,000 crore this year, the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Sebi) is considering a slew of measures to ensure that retail investors find it easier to invest in IPOs. The infrastructure committee under Sebi is scanning the investment norms in detail so that some of them can be amended to facilitate investors and at the same time avoid the allotment crisis faced during the ONGC public offer last year, sources said. 

 Mumbai, Jan. 21: All major bourses, including Bombay Stock Exchange and National Stock Exchange, were closed today on account of Id-ul-Zuha. The foreign exchange, money and oils and oilseeds markets were also closed. 

 New Delhi, Jan. 21: The board of Infosys has allotted 75,291 shares at par value of Rs 5 per share under the ESOP scheme, the company informed the BSE.

 New Delhi, Jan. 21: BSNL does not plan to raise charges, despite suffering a loss of over Rs 1,250 crore due to the new tariff regime announced by Trai. However, the telecom major may cut some rural projects to make up for the losses.

 New Delhi, Jan. 21: Seeking a level playing field with SEZs, export oriented units have demanded restoration of tax holiday under the sunset clause, exemption from central sales tax, state taxes and levies.




